    "name": "StableCoin-MaturityLadder-30d",
    "description": "ACTUS Stablecoin: MATURITY LADDER MODEL (6.3) — T-bill roll decision engine.\n\nScenario: Adaptive reserve management during escalating de-peg risk.\n  Issuer: StableCoinA, $100M outstanding supply\n  PEG_RISK_SCORE evolves: 0→50 peak→recovery\n\nDECISION TREE (from MaturityLadderModel.java):\n  Score < 15  → NORMAL_ROLL      (signal=0.0, T-bill renews at current tenor)\n  15 <= < 30  → SHORTEN_TENOR    (signal=0.25, shorten maturity to 4-week)\n  30 <= < 45  → CASH_RETENTION   (signal=0.50, hold as cash, do not roll)\n  Score >= 45 → EMERGENCY_LIQUIDATE (signal=1.0, liquidate all to cash)\n\nKEY DYNAMICS:\n  Days 1-8:   Score 0-12 → all maturities roll normally\n  Days 9-13:  Score 15-28 → tenor shortening begins (26W→4W)\n  Days 14-17: Score 30-44 → cash retention mode (stop all rolling)\n  Day 18-20:  Score 45-50 → emergency: sell T-bills at market\n  Days 21-30: Recovery: score declines → resume normal operations\n\nRegulatory context:\n  GENIUS Act: WAM <= 93 days requirement\n  Cash retention at WAM > 93 triggers regulatory action\n  Emergency liquidation = fire-sale risk on treasury portfolio\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
